          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                                        <date>January 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Friend <addressee>Isaac;</addressee></p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">'tis a very long time since I have written<lb/> to
                                        you, and you care very little about it I dare say for
                                        the<lb/> letters of an old married woman possess very
                                        little<lb/> interest to young unmarried <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >gents</hi>, however full of human<lb/> frailty
                                        and the vanity all predominant in woman I<lb/> for truth
                                        send you another one of my scrawls, but fear me<lb/> 'twill
                                        meet the same treatment as the last—in the first<lb/> place
                                        my rapience<add>?</add>, I imagine you are unlike those
                                        sun-<lb/>shine friends which sheds a 'lustre on our way when
                                        we are<lb/> prosperous and adds to the darkness when
                                        adversity<lb/> surrounds us—therefore I am induced to make
                                        known our<lb/> deplorable situation—you know my husband is
                                        striving in<lb/>
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName> to get up a school, and that
                                        he has met with<lb/> little encouragement, ten scholars is
                                        all he has not enough<lb/> to pay his expenses there, and I
                                        am left with my family<lb/> without the means of support, I
                                        have wished and tried<lb/> to procure some boarders but I
                                        cannot hear of any who<lb/> care about <sic>cosher</sic>
                                        living and as to christians I fear<lb/> they would not be
                                        satisfied with our mode of living now<lb/> I wish you to
                                        tell me <hi rend="underline">candidly</hi> what you think
                                        will<lb/> be the result of <persName>Eleaser's</persName>
                                        undertaking is there a prospect<lb/> of an increase from any
                                        other quarter than the people<lb/> of <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName>, all such matters take time but
                                        unfortunately<lb/> we are so poor that time cannot be spared
                                        in an-<lb/>ticipation. I think perhaps were he to ask less
                                        price</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>for younger children he might do better_do dear
                                                  <persName>Isaac</persName><lb/> interest yourself
                                        for us and if you think there is a better<lb/> opening in
                                        your city or elsewhere let us know and if<lb/> a boarding
                                        house would succeed in either place. I cannot but believe
                                        that our merciful Father will not<lb/> suffer those to want
                                        who so <sic>confidantly</sic> depend in<lb/> his mercy to
                                        relieve their necessities and actively strive<lb/> with all
                                        their energies to live—I regret my inability<lb/> at present
                                        to pay you for those two prayer books, but<lb/> hope to do
                                        so at some future day, and also that I<lb/> cannot afford to
                                        be any longer a subscriber to the<lb/> publication
                                        society—when I can renew it I will let you<lb/> know—should
                                        any one come this way who wishes to<lb/> live
                                                  <sic>cosher</sic> whilst <sic>her</sic> I
                                                  <sic>shold</sic> be glad to have them<lb/> stop
                                        with us—your Cousin <persName>Myer</persName> reports he was
                                        engaged<lb/> to me and that I am his Cousin, so of course am
                                        yours<lb/> he has quite a pretty daughter I am told—I need not<lb/>
                                        <sic>as</sic> you not to expose the contents of this as I
                                        well<lb/> know you will only do that which will be
                                        right—</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">God bless and send you better health and
                                        better<lb/> fortune than your poor friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(11)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Block</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">remembrance to all friends—love <sic>“</sic>to my Aunt<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mark's</persName> and A new house and offer my
                                        congratulations<lb/> to them—I just recollected that I told
                                                  <persName>Rosalie</persName><lb/> to pay you for
                                        those books did she do<lb/> so?</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>P<hi rend="underline">a</hi></placeName>
                              </p>
